    <stitle>POWER STEERING GEAR: TRW/ROSS-TAS 40, 55, 65 AND 85 - IDENTIFICATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>IDENTIFICATION</title>
        <para>The steering gear specification number and date code are stamped on a machined surface opposite the input
            shaft of every TAS gear (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0500302">Figure 2</hotlnk>). An example date code would be 012-90; this means the gear was
            built on the 12th day of 1990.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0500302" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0500302" filename="../figg05/G0500302.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 2. Steering Gear Specification Number</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0500303">Figure 3</hotlnk>
            for the breakdown of the steering gear components.
        </para>
